  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, the model employs a low-rank decomposition approach to break down multimodal tensors into smaller ones and utilizes a gating mechanism to control the significance of each decomposed tensor, enabling effective fusion of multimodal information.Multimodal Factorization Model (MFM) [25]: MFM captures interactions between modalities using factorization, exhibiting flexible generative capabilities by adjusting independent factors and reconstructing missing modalities.",
    "It represents each modality as a set of factors whose interactions produce joint features, which are then reconstructed for missing modalities using deep neural networks.Modality-Invariant and Modality-Specific Representations (MISA) [26]: MISA learns and fuses representations of different modalities by integrating distributional similarity, orthogonal loss, reconstruction loss, and task prediction loss.",
    "Applicable to a variety of multimodal data tasks such as audiovisual speech synthesis and emotion recognition, this approach focuses on harmonizing modality-invariant features with modality-specific nuances.Self-Supervised Multimodal Learning Framework (Self-MM) [27]: Employed for multimodal emotion analysis, Self-MM adopts self-supervised tasks to learn representations of different modalities.",
    "The framework assigns unimodal tasks with auto-generated labels to each modality to learn effective modality-specific features.",
    "These representations are then fused to train classifiers for the emotion analysis task."
  ],
